cs.NE, cs.OH, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SY

The paper proposes an evolutionary algorithm for bilevel optimization problems, which is a subfield of optimization and computational intelligence. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also uses quadratic approximations and hybridizes classical optimization with evolutionary methods, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.OH (Optimization and Control) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper deals with optimization problems, which is a common topic in cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.SY (Systems and Control).
